  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><img src="/media/13070746/cefalu.jpg?width=848&amp;height=404&amp;mode=max" alt="Italy Beach Holidays" width="848" height="404" data-udi="umb://media/9d65bbd1b8084813b4db94a0a5abb1d6" /></p>
<p>Bella Italia, the land of pasta, pizza and stunning beaches. Offering nearly 8,000 kilometres of coastline, this beautiful boot-shaped paradise offers countless opportunities for beach lovers to bask in the sun and sink their toes in the sand.</p>
<p>The beaches here are so clean and well-serviced that they’ve earned the prestigious <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.blueflag.global/" target="_blank" title="Blue Flag Status">Blue Flag status</a>. And let’s not forget the jaw-dropping beauty of Italy's iconic coastal towns, with <a rel="noopener" href="https://whc.unesco.org/en/statesparties/it" target="_blank" title="Italy UNESCO">UNESCO awards</a> for both natural and historical significance.</p>
<p>Whether you’re discovering the rocky shoreline Cinque Terre or lounging on the glamorous beaches of the Amalfi Coast, you’ll be living the dolce a vita.</p>
<p>If you’re looking for a beach holiday that offers more than just sand and sunscreen, then check out some of our top picks for Italy beach holidays. You can also dive into a <a data-udi="umb://document/4265501ed34b4842883a8cfc5cd5cf1f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4265501ed34b4842883a8cfc5cd5cf1f}" title="Italy Multi-Centre Holidays">multi-centre </a>trip and experience the ultimate combination of sun, sand and bustling city life.</p>
<p>View our favourite Italy beach holidays below.</p>
<p> </p>
<h2>Beach holidays in Cinque Terre</h2>
<p><img style="width: 848px; height: 385px;" src="/media/13095455/monterosso-beach-cinque-terre-italy.jpg?width=848&amp;height=385&amp;mode=max" alt="Italy beach holidays" data-udi="umb://media/554cd84bad2b4093ab96d74f1ed1c8c8" /></p>
<p>Our holidays in Cinque Terre offer the ultimate beach holiday experience, with a diverse coastline featuring small bays, all surrounded by the turquoise waters of the Ligurian Sea. </p>
<p>The region is characterised by its charming seaside villages, where rows of brightly coloured buildings hug the rugged coastline. We absolutely love the clusters of multi-coloured houses - a stunning contrast to the backdrop of majestic mountains.</p>
<p>Monterosso boasts two long beaches with sand and pebbles, including the famous Fegina beach with its iconic rock formation and vibrant umbrellas. Or for a quieter and more secluded option, you can head to the old town beach and Spiaggia Tragagia, near the small harbour of Monterosso. It's just a few steps from the historical centre, or a quick ferry ride away. This peaceful and serene beach provides the perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of the main beaches.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/79a94ac27eda4c2ea223bc0fe7fd99b6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/79a94ac27eda4c2ea223bc0fe7fd99b6}" title="Cinque Terre" class="c-btn">View Cinque Terre holidays</a></p>
<p> </p>
<h3>Our recommended beach hotel in Cinque Terre</h3>
<h3><a data-udi="umb://document/d5d0b5db289244a19d1adf9de784abc9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d5d0b5db289244a19d1adf9de784abc9}" title="Grand Hotel Portovenere">Grand Hotel Portovenere</a></h3>
<p><img style="width: 848px; height: 385px;" src="/media/13095457/grand-hotel-portovenere-corner-room-1.jpg?width=848&amp;height=385&amp;mode=max" alt="italy beach holidays" data-udi="umb://media/442c71d1591b4fa593dbc29f0913342a" /></p>
<p>This hotel offers stunning sea views and in conveniently located right on the doorstep of Cinque Terre. With regular boats departing from the harbour in front of the hotel, exploring the coastline is effortless.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/d5d0b5db289244a19d1adf9de784abc9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d5d0b5db289244a19d1adf9de784abc9}" title="Grand Hotel Portovenere" class="c-btn">Find out more</a></p>]]></bodyText>
